						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>I just made them up <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_robot-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> I try to make it a habit not to post suggestions unless I can also post ideas about implementing it/making it better so I took five minutes and whipped something up. Or maybe it's a secret desire to become the Brodder of Instrument Crafting. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_robot-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Sometimes I don't think people realize how hard it is to find a good selection of instruments. At 65 it's still impossible for me to find an upgrade for my Immaculate Shell Horn that I've used since shortly after Velious was released. In fact there are *no* droppable upgrades to the ISH, which bites because the horn is Secondary only. My only options are Elemental BP, Blazing Horn of&nbsp;Fire&nbsp;(big Yeah Rights for the casual bard), 1000 LDON points for the Lost Traveller Horn, or spending days camping the rare drop off a rare spawn in Valor for Ornate Horn of the Valorous. Bards are chained to their epics far beyond the point where all other classes have bagged them, simply because we have&nbsp;so few&nbsp;alternatives.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>There are only 111 bard focus items (read: instruments) currently discovered. Only 80 of those have mods higher than epic. 20 of those 80 come from Tier 4 or Time or places like Vex Thal or NToV which the average bard has little chance of seeing much less seeing that particular item drop. So this gives 60 options for instruments. 39 of those 60 are SECONDARY only, which means we only have 21 options for instruments which don't take up BOTH our weapon slots.</P>
																		
